value.doc: Logger that use the javascript console object.

log ?section ?logger ~level message logs a message.section defaults to Lwt_log_jsSectionmain. If logger is not specified, then the default one is used instead (see Lwt_log_jsdefault).If exn is provided, then its string representation (= Printexc.to_string exn) will be append to the message, and if possible the backtrace will also be logged.If inspect is provided, it will be append to the message.location contains the location of the logging directive, it is of the form (file_name, line, column).
log_f is the same as log except that it takes a format string
Same as Lwt_log_jslog but ignore the resulting thread.
Same as Lwt_log_jslog_f but ignore the resulting thread.

unit.comment: The following functions are the same as Lwt_log_jslog except that their name determines which level is used.For example info msg is the same as log ~level:Info msg.
